messages.text: Just doing a little pre-exercise stretching.
SO when do you think you’re going start the “burn game,” on my ex-fiancee?
You didn’t tell me you were engaged.
I picked out a ring. It was a Marquise.
Well, it would be nice to start making back that investment.
Funny you should reach out. I’m about to start the game right now.
Yes. In order to chase your lovely lady through the park :)
I took the info you gave me and started a journal of her whereabouts.
She runs the park loop every Sunday, 6.25 miles.
Because apparently she only ever half-completes anything.
How do you plan to pick her up?
She runs a steady eight and half minute mile.
I plan to be lying right across her path recovering from a nasty fall.
What makes you think she’ll stop?
She’s an empathetic sort. She’ll stop.
Fine. How’s it going with you?
Are you checking up on me?
Don’t want to know how the story’s coming?
I’m the best. Because I care. About the story.
So, now that you mention it. How is the story coming along?
I’m about to meet a new source.
And I have a woman who’s willing to discuss what happened to her.
Apparently, but the boyfriend felt guilty and spilled the beans.
So naturally, she wants to bring these a-holes to justice.
She has a bunch of old text messages saved.
But she’ll only give them to me in print.
She’s afraid of being sued. It’s fine. I’m meeting her in the park on my run.
I want minute by minute updates.
Ha ha. Just let me know once you have the file.
Not yet. Still working up a sweat.
That’s right. Gotta look authentic. Plus it’s manly.
I don’t have weird sweat lines.
If you’re running, how are you texting?
Got my watch on, synced to my phone, also monitors my heart rate.
Should I let you know if it goes up when I see your ex? :)
Approaching mile three. Time to fake an injury.
Should be coming round the bend any minute.
I thought I was letting YOU know when I got the file.
I thought I was getting minute by minute updates.
She’s supposed to meet me around mile three.
Is there like a code or something? How do you know what she looks like?
Shut up. Don’t ruin this for me. Is she there?
She’s supposed to be wearing a sun dress and a straw hat.
Think I see her in the distance.
There’s someone else here. Her hat just blew off.
A gentleman doesn’t let a lady’s hat blow away.
Too late. Just going to have to hide behind this hat.
What happened! Did you get it?
And there’s some weirdo with a straw hat over his face.
I thought she was wearing the straw hat?
What are you going to do???
Good news is she didn’t see my face.
Didn’t know a girl in a sundress could run so fast.
Are you catching up to her?
Just about. Think this path will cut her off…
She's almost out of the park.
Good news. I got her number :)
Oh, I’m injured. But it’s not fake. Ambulance is on it’s way.
Ran right into your ex. Tripped. Twisted my ankle on the way down.
Now it’s the size of a grapefruit.
I’m not paying extra for that.
So how did you get her number?
Not too bad. The other guy got the worst of it ;)
I felt bad so I gave him my number.
That’s not what this file I’m holding says.
She dropped it as she ran away.
I was picking it up when he ran into me.
There’s a picture of him in here and guess who he looks like?
My runner friend who just got my number.
Looks like the game is on. :)
